(176, 'Dong Hun Lee', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/6669549a2303c.증명 (1).jpg', 'Department of Education, Sungkyunkwan University, Seoul', 'South Korea', '<p>Prof. Dong Hun Lee has been a distinguished faculty member at Sungkyunkwan University in Korea since 2013, where he serves as a Professor and Coordinator of the Counseling Psychology &amp; Counselor Education Program in the Department of Education. He has made significant contributions to the field of counseling psychology, both in academia and on a national level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since 2016, Prof. Lee has been an active member of the National Law Affairs &amp; Protection Council under the Ministry of Justice in the Korean Government, where he has influenced policies related to psychological services and legal protections. In 2023, he was appointed President of the National Counseling Council for University Students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prof. Lee received the Minister&#39;s Award from the Ministry of Justice in 2022.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prof. Lee has a prolific publication record, with numerous articles and research papers that have significantly advanced the field of counseling psychology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Research Interest : Trauma, Post-Traumatic Growth, Resilience, Suicide and Self-harm Behaviors, Crisis &amp; Disaster Psychology/Counseling, Prisoners/Ex-Convictors&rsquo; Counseling, Single Parents Family, ADHD</p>', 3, '', '', '', 9, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(177, 'Joshua Beneite Martí', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/66696db0d95ba.IMG_1821-removebg.png', 'Department of Comparative Education and History of Education, University of Valencia', 'Spain', '<p>Joshua Beneite Mart&iacute; is a lecturer at the Faculty of Philosophy and Educational Sciences of the University of Valencia (Spain), in the Department of Comparative Education and History of Education. He has a PhD in Ethics and Democracy and a Master&#39;s degree in Ethical Governance of Artificial Intelligence. Currently, &nbsp;works on Service-Learning projects in his community. On the other hand, he investigates the impact of Artificial Intelligence on society and education, as well as its application to the Service-Learning methodology. He has published texts on International Education, analyzing the context of neocolonialist education, in addition to various articles on philosophy and ecological philosophy.</p>', 3, '', '', '', 1, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(178, 'Rowena Hoi Yee Liu', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/66696e0fa00a3.Rowena 2024.jpg', 'Faculty of Education, The University of Hong Kong.', 'Hong Kong SAR China', '<p>Ms Rowena Hoi Yee LIU&nbsp;is a lecturer in experiential learning at the University of Hong Kong Faculty of Education. She taught at The Education University of Hong Kong, The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology, and secondary schools. She previously worked as a part-time teaching kit designer for the Education Bureau. Apart from teaching, she provides on-site support to schools for different university-school partnership projects, including projects on &lsquo;School-based Support Program for Developing Curriculum Materials to Enhance Teaching the PSHE KLA in the English Medium&rsquo; and &lsquo;Supporting Schools and Universities for 21st Century Learning: Partnerships for the Future&rsquo; etc. She obtained her dual master&rsquo;s degrees in Education (specializing in curriculum design and implementation) and Liberal Studies. Her research interests include experiential learning / life-wide learning, Community of Practice, 21st century skills and values development in school contexts, ethics, spiritual and values education, curriculum design, field experience and novice teacher development, etc.&nbsp;</p>', 3, '', '', '', 8, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(179, 'Chi Cheung Ruby Yang', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/66696e64b1ccc.4.3-YANG-Chi-Cheung-Ruby_v2.jpg', 'Faculty of Education, The University of Hong Kong', 'Hong Kong SAR China', '<p>Dr. Chi Cheung Ruby YANG is an experienced teacher educator in English language education. She is currently a lecturer at The Faculty of Education, The University of Hong Kong, where she teaches courses related to English language teaching methodology and English language curriculum. She completed her PhD in Applied Linguistics at Lancaster University. Her major research interests include gender representation in English language teaching materials and flipped classroom pedagogy. She has a range of publications in academic journals. She is also actively involved in the editorial boards of a number of journals.</p>', 3, '', '', '', 14, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(180, 'Mirca Montanari', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/66696eec08cb4.Mirca Montanari_page-0001.jpg', 'Department of Humanities, Communication and Tourism, University of Tuscia, Viterbo', 'Italy', '<p>Dr. Mirca Montanari, Ph.D. in Humanistic Studies, is a Research fellow in Pedagogy and Special Education at the University University of Tuscia, where she teaches Special Education and Pedagogy, General and Inclusive Education, Pedagogy, special of integrated classroom group management.&nbsp; Her research topics include inclusive school processes, special educational needs, support teacher training, and inclusive orientation at the university. She is the author of various essays and papers in scientific journals and books. Among her most recent publications is Educarsi in un mondo operoso. Percorsi emancipativi in prospettiva inclusiva (edited by, Trento, Erickson, 2019); I bisogni educativi nella scuola e i contesti inclusivi (Milan, FrancoAngeli, 2020) winner of the Siped 2023 prize; Contesti scolastici e sociali in prospettiva inclusiva (Rome, Aracne, 2020); La narrazione nel processo formativo (edited by, in collaboration with R. Persi, Rome, Aracne, 2021); Dialoghi pedagogic nell&#39;ipercomplessit&agrave; (edited by, in collaboration with R. Persi, Pisa, ETS, 2022); Orientamento e formazione universitaria.In prospettiva inclusiva (Rome, Anicia, 2023).</p>', 3, '', '', '', 13, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(181, 'Mary Koutselini', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/66696f704eb7f.174376_545758302_7838179_n[1].jpg', 'Department of Education, University of Cyprus.', 'Cyprus', '<p>Dr Mary Koutselini is Professor of Curriculum and Instruction, Chair holder of the UNESCO chair in Gender Equality and Women&rsquo;s Empowerment of the University of Cyprus (2008-2023), and a regular member of the European Academy of Arts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She studied Greek Philology (Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Greece). Curriculum Development and Evaluation (State University of New York, U.S.A) and Curriculum Development and Educational Policy (National Kapodistrian University of Athens). Her research interests include: Curriculum and educational policy; Action Research; Differentiation of Teaching and Learning; Gender Studies; Teacher and trainers&rsquo; Education, Development and Evaluation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She participated as an expert in working groups of the European Commission and advisory global, European, and national boards and networks and also as a National representative of International Networks (CICE- International Socrates Network on Citizenship Teaching and Research; IEA International Association of the Assessment of Educational Achievement). She served as head person of the Center of Learning of the University of Cyprus, of the Department of Education and as an external evaluator of Universities, Research, and academic staff in Cyprus and abroad. 2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She is the Coordinator of 20 International, European and National Research programs in the areas of her specialization and is an active member of a number of national, European and international academic associations and editorial boards of scientific journals. She has also been the founder and coordinator of the University of Cyprus post-graduate program &lsquo;Curriculum, Instruction and Comparative Education&rsquo; and of the interdisciplinary program &ldquo;Gender Studies&rdquo;. She has authored 15 books and more than 250 articles and invited chapters in scientific refereed journals and books. She is also a member of the Editorial Board of a number of Scientific Academic Journals. She served as President, Vice president and member in a number of independent Councils and Advisory Committees in Cyprus and abroad. Since 2015 has been the President of the first Council of the Cyprus Agency for Quality Assurance and Accreditation of Higher Education (CYQAA), an independent authority, registered in EQAR.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 3, '', '', '', 10, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(182, 'Antonia Samara', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/66697008b5271.samara photo.jpg', 'Department of Educational Studies, School of Philosophy, National and Kapodistrian University of Athens.', 'Greece', '<p>Dr. Antonia Samara is a member of the teaching staff within the Department of Educational Studies at the School of Philosophy, National and Kapodistrian University of Athens (NKUA). Her area of expertise lies in Comparative Education and Lifelong Learning. Dr. Samara has contributed extensively to research projects focusing on the European Dimension in Education, Skills and Competencies, Schools as Learning Organisations and Communities, and Access to Higher Education.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She has co-authored one book and served as co-editor for a collective volume. Additionally, she has authored and co-authored numerous journal articles, chapters in collective volumes, reports, and publications for teacher training. Her research interests encompass Lifelong Learning Policies, Competences, Lifelong Learning and Higher Education, Education Governance, Teachers&#39; Continuous Professional Development, and Assessment and Quality in Education, with publications available in both Greek and English.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Samara is actively involved in academic societies, serving as a member of the Executive Committee of the Greek Comparative and International Education Society. Furthermore, she contributes to the academic community as a member of the Editorial Board of the bilingual academic journal &quot;Comparative and International Education Review.&quot;</p>', 3, '', '', '', 12, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(183, 'Bahareh Abedin', NULL, 'board-member-image/jblm/6669762f6925f.bahar-pic.jpg', 'Department of Executive Management, Faculty of Economics and Administrative Sciences, University of Mazandaran', 'Iran', '<p>Dr. Bahareh Abedin is an Assistant Professor in the Department of Executive Management, Faculty of Economic and Administrative Sciences, at the University of Mazandaran. With a multidisciplinary background in business management, strategic management, and marketing, Dr. Bahareh Abedin specializes in business analysis and strategic planning for small and medium-sized businesses. Currently, Dr. Bahareh Abedin holds the positions of Director of the Executive Management and Business Department at the university and Secretary of the University and Industry Relations Committee. Dr. Bahareh Abedin obtained a PhD in Strategic Management from the Faculty of Management at Tarbiat Modares University of Iran. Prior to joining academia, Dr. Bahareh Abedin gained practical experience in the fields of sales, marketing, and management consulting. This real-world exposure has significantly influenced Dr. Bahareh Abedin&#39;s research, which is primarily focused on the behavioral aspects of strategic management and the relationship between industry and academia. Dr. Bahareh Abedin&#39;s research approach is grounded in behavioral and management theories, aiming to address practical challenges faced by businesses. In addition to her teaching and research responsibilities, Dr. Bahareh Abedin serves as the Internal Manager of Mazandaran University&#39;s Journal of Sustainable Human Resource Management. She also works as a strategic planning consultant for the university and industry, leveraging her expertise to bridge the gap between academia and the business world. Dr. Bahareh Abedin has successfully supervised several HDR (Higher Degree by Research) students to completion and is currently available to supervise research students in the following areas:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Research Supervision Areas:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Analysis</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Behavioral Strategic Management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Neurostrategy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Industry and University</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Industry and university connection</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teaching:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strategic management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Analysis</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Entrepreneurship</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Research methodology</p>', 5, '', '', '', 31, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(184, 'Patrick Ebewo', NULL, 'board-member-image/jblm/666976ee04d7b.Dr Patrick Ebewo (1).png', 'Department of Management and Entrepreneurship, Faculty of Management Sciences, Tshwane University of Technology', 'South Africa', '<p>Dr Patrick Ebewo is a distinguished enterprise and entrepreneurship development expert who significantly impacts academia and social initiatives within the Southern African Development Community (SADC) region. With over a decade of experience in academia and industry, he has collaborated with private and public enterprises, playing a pivotal role in shaping entrepreneurship programs to foster positive societal change. Dr. Ebewo&#39;s educational background is robust, with a Doctoral degree in Business Administration specializing in Entrepreneurship Development. His academic journey includes a cum laude Diploma in Accounting and Business Studies, a Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Finance, a cum laude B Tech in Management, and a Master&#39;s in Entrepreneurship. These qualifications have underpinned his career and his contributions to the field.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the Head of the Department of Management and Entrepreneurship at Tshwane University of Technology (TUT), Dr. Ebewo brings extensive experience and expertise to shaping academic curricula and guiding aspiring entrepreneurs. His leadership extends to the TUT Centre for Entrepreneurship Development, where he spearheads initiatives to support sustainable emerging businesses. Under his direction, the Centre facilitates innovative business ideas, cultivates entrepreneurial competence, and fosters a culture of peer support and networking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His leadership at the TUT Centre for Entrepreneurship Development earned the esteemed 2023 Presidential Award for Innovative Solutions in Small Business Development, acknowledging his exceptional contributions to entrepreneurship. Dr. Ebewo founded the Bopangpeo Business Accelerator NPC, the Tshwane University Technology Arts (Creative Enterprise) Incubator, a UNESCO Chair in Cultural Policy and Sustainable Development for Southern Africa, and the Centre for Entrepreneurship Development. These initiatives have significantly shaped the region&#39;s entrepreneurship landscape. Dr. Ebewo&rsquo;s contributions have garnered numerous accolades, reflecting his commitment to excellence and innovation. He is a recognized Mandela Rhodes Scholar (Cohort 2012, South Africa), an esteemed Harambe Entrepreneur Associate (HEA&#39; 2013, USA), and a World Economic Forum Global Shaper (Tshwane Hub, South Africa) for the 2013/2014 term.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Beyond his academic roles, Dr. Ebewo is officially recognized by the South African Institute of Professional Accountants (SAIPA) as a Professional Business Advisor (SA). He holds memberships with the Southern Africa Institute of Management Scientists (SAIMS) and the research portfolio committee of Coaches and Mentors of South Africa (COMENSA). These affiliations underscore his dedication to advancing his fields of expertise and contributing to the broader professional community.</p>', 5, '', '', '', 30, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(185, 'Monika Krajcovicova', NULL, 'board-member-image/rer/666979d74ef0a.IMG_3946.jpeg', 'School of Education, The University of Notre Dame, Sydney', 'Australia', '<p>Dr Monika Krajcovicova is a Senior Lecturer in Early Childhood Education at the School of Education, The University of Notre Dame Australia. Monika specializes in interculturality, educational equity and social justice, and internationalization within higher education. Her research endeavours are dedicated to enhancing educational practices, policies, and experiences for children from diverse cultural backgrounds and supporting disadvantaged communities. Additionally, she is committed to supporting and enhancing the educational experiences of students in university environments, aiming to contribute to the creation of an inclusive, supportive, and globally aware academic community. Monika has served as an International Editorial Board Member of the Social Pathology and Prevention (S.P.P.) journal and as a Management Committee Member of the Multicultural Families Organisation Inc. in Gold Coast, Australia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDr Monika Krajcovicova has held various leadership roles in higher education institutions. She served as the Coordinator for International Relationships (2007-2010) before becoming the Vice-Dean of International Relationships (2010-2011) at the Faculty of Education, University of Presov in Slovakia. Furthermore, she was the Program Director (2015-2017) for the Graduate Certificate in Early Childhood Education and Care, Graduate Diploma of Early Childhood Education, and Master of Early Childhood Education at the School of Education and Professional Studies, Griffith University, Australia. As a Program Co-coordinator at the School of Education, The University of Notre Dame Australia, Monika assisted in the Bachelor of Primary Education program.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDr Krajcovicova has been recognized with numerous teaching commendations, including the 2022 Academic Director&#39;s Commendations for Teaching and Learning at Griffith College, as well as Teaching Commendations in 2021 and 2018, and the Academic Provost Commendation in 2015, from Griffith University in Australia. Additionally, Monika has been the recipient of several prestigious awards and fellowships, such as the 2011 Endeavour Awards Research Fellowships at Monash University in Australia, the 2010 Erasmus Teaching Staff Mobility Programme at Queen Maud University College of Early Childhood Education in Norway, the 2009 The Lifelong Learning Programme (LLP) at Roma Tre University in Italy, the 2008 Ruth Crawford Mitchell Scholarship at the University of Pittsburgh in the United States, and the 2006 National Scholarship (MINERVA) Programme at Manchester Metropolitan University in the United Kingdom.</p>', 3, '', '', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0856-5973', 11, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(186, 'Cosimo Magazzino', NULL, 'board-member-image/seer/666a84eb2f53b.Piedmont Park.png', 'Professor of Economic Policy, European Economic Policy, and Environmental and Energy Economics, Department of Political Science, Roma Tre University', 'Italy', '<p>He is currently a Professor of economic policy, European economic policy, and Environmental and Energy Economics in the Department of Political Science, Roma Tre University (Italy); econometrics for Financial Markets in the MEMOTEF Department, Sapienza-University of Rome (Italy); and environmental and Tourism Economics at &quot;Niccol&ograve; Cusano&quot; University (Italy). He is a member of the Ph.D. Council on Political Science, Roma Tre University (Italy). He coordinated the Ministry of Economy and Finance (MEF) Research program &ldquo;Quality of public finances and impact on potential output&rdquo;. He has taught and/or is teaching Development Economics, Econometrics, Econometrics for Financial Markets, Economic Policy, European Economic Policy, Environmental and Energy Economics, Environmental and Land Economics, Economics of Globalization, Economics and Development Policy, Health Economics, Introductory Econometrics, Mathematics for Social Sciences, and STATA Laboratory in: the undergraduate and graduate programs in the Department of Political Science, Roma Tre University (Italy); MEMOTEF Department, Sapienza-University of Rome (Italy); &quot;Niccol&ograve; Cusano&quot; University; (Italy) Faculty of Economics, University of International Studies of Rome-UNINT (Italy); School of Political Sciences and Trade Union Relations, University of International Studies of Rome-UNINT (Italy); Department of Economics, Management and Business Law, University of Bari (Italy); the Ph.D. Council on Government of the Enterprise, Administration and Society in the International Dimension, University of Teramo (Italy); Environmental Science Research Division-ESRD, University of Reading (UK); Faculty of Economics and Business Administration, West University of Timisoara (Romania); Zeppelin University (Germany).</p>', 3, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=HRRZ1nMAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=54405918800', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3176-9838', 2, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(187, 'Alexandra Alexandropoulou', NULL, 'board-member-image/jblm/666abde0b2aab.Alexandropoulou.jpg', 'Department of Business Administration, University of Piraeus', 'Greece', 'Dr. Alexandra Alexandropoulou is an Assistant Professor of \"Environmental Management and Sustainable Development - Economic and Technical Analysis\" at the Department of Business Administration of the University of Piraeus.\r\nShe holds a Ph.D. in Business Administration from the University of Piraeus. \r\nShe has more than two decades of professional experience in the public sector, holding executive positions (Head of Department/Direction) in the fields of Environmental Planning, Planning and Development in a large Local Government Organization. Her experience mainly concerns operational programmes’ planning and design, preparation of sustainable development and integrated local development plans, planning, management and implementation of co-funded programmes national and European programmes (including Urban Innovative Actions, Urbact II, Horizon 2020, FP6, Interreg IIB-CADSES, Daphne, Rights Equality Citizenship, Progress, etc.).\r\nHer scientific and research interests focus on Environmental Management, Sustainable Development, Technology and Innovation Management, Development of Business Plans, Corporate Governance, Sustainable Development Business models, Sustainable Development and Entrepreneurship.', 5, '', '', '', 32, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(188, 'José Carlos Metrolho', NULL, 'board-member-image/cie/666c31cfd8bd5.12.png', 'Technical-scientific Unit of Informatics, School of Technology, Polytechnic Institute of Castelo Branco', 'Portugal', 'Dr. José Carlos Metrolho is a Coordinator Professor (Polytechnic Teacher) at the Informatics Department (Technical-scientific Unit) at Polytechnic Institute of Castelo Branco, PT. He holds a PhD in Industrial Informatics (2008). He has been teaching since 1995 and authoring several conference papers, journal papers, and book chapters since 1997. His main research interests include software engineering, mobile computing, low-code development, programming languages, and computer science education. He has served as President of the department and Director of the School on different occasions, among other positions.', 4, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=TR9dl2AAAAAJ', '', '', 9, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(189, 'Michelle Buchberger', NULL, 'board-member-image/ijerm/6671110f1f9e7.1.png', 'Department of Interdisciplinary Studies, Miami University of Ohio.', 'United States', 'Michelle Phillips Buchberger holds a BA in English and Music from the West London Institute, a PGCE in secondary education from Nottingham University, an MA in English Literature from the Open University, and a PhD in English Literature from Brunel University, London. \r\n\r\nSince joining Miami in the Department of Interdisciplinary Studies in 2014, she has taught classes in Integrative Studies, Liberal Studies, English Literature, and Film. Her recent publications include the co-authored Introduction to Interdisciplinary Studies (3rd Ed., 2019), which is currently being revised for its 4th edition, “Parasite and Identity in the “End Times”\r\nAn Interpretation of Bong Joon-Ho’s Film through the Lens of Slavoj Žižek” in Parasite: A philosophical exploration (Eds. Botz -Bernstein and Stamatellos, 2022), and “The Cult of the Charismatic Leader: D. H. Lawrence’s Leadership Novels and the Authoritarian Temptation” D.H. Lawrence Review (2023).', 1, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=3esE5DYAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=57210551706', '', 8, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(190, 'Yuesheng Gao', NULL, 'board-member-image/cie/667116e17a888.YG_1.jpg', 'Department of Chemical Engineering, Michigan Technological University. Houghton.', 'United States', 'Yuesheng Gao is a highly accomplished professional in chemical and mining engineering. He earned a Bachelor\'s and Master\'s degree in Mining Engineering from Central South University in China and a Ph.D. in Chemical Engineering from Michigan Technological University. His doctoral research included innovative work in mineral surface modification and characterization.\r\nSince 2010, Dr. Gao has excelled in the mining chemical industry, specializing in reagent development and mineral-processing flowsheet design. In 2021, he joined Arkema ArrMaz mining lab, leading projects on critical minerals like lithium and rare earth elements. His outstanding performance recently led to his promotion to Lead Engineer.\r\nDr. Gao also serves as secretary for the Florida Society for Mining, Metallurgy & Exploration (SME) and is an editorial board member for several journals. He has published 25 papers cited over 1100 times and holds 8 international patents.', 4, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=Ies4vVUAAAAJ', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=57188732247', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8796-4408', 6, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(191, 'Anita Boros', NULL, 'board-member-image/ijerm/667169d40bf1f.88X8gX37tynPKud8bfqYqR33UNn7zUzsnQDGYeQP.jpg', 'Institute of Agricultural and Food Economics, Hungarian University of Agriculture and Life Sciences, Godollo, Hungary', 'Hungary', 'Prof. Dr. Anita Boros is a professor at the National University of Public Service, the Hungarian University of Physical Education and Sports Sciences, and the Hungarian University of Agricultural and Life Sciences. She graduated in 2001 from the College of Public Administration, and in 2005 as a lawyer at the Eötvös Loránd University, and in 2010 at the Andrássy Gyula German Language University, the comparative state and jurisprudence LL.M program. She obtained a doctorate (PhD) degree in 2009 and a habilitated doctorate in 2016. During her career, she has held senior positions in several state administrative and judicial bodies. She has also performed the duties of head of department and head of the institute in recent years. She is the editor and member of the editorial board of several Hungarian scientific journals. (E.g.: Kodifikáció és Közigazgatás, Közigazgatási Eljárási Jogi Közlemények, Közbeszerzési Értesítő Plusz) In addition, she is a member of several bodies, such as a member of the Hungarian Lawyers\' Association, a member of the public body of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences and a member of the Circular Economy Interdepartmental Standing Committee of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences. She is a member of the RENEUAL European Research Network, the president of the Public Administration Procedural Law Association, and the leader of the Greenology Green Innovation and Sustainability Knowledge Center. Dr. Boros has been the leader of several types of research in the past period, mainly in the areas of public administrative authority procedures, green economy, circular economy and sustainability. \r\n\r\nSo far, she has helped the work of nearly twenty doctoral students. Seven of them have already obtained a scientific degree at the Hungarian universities. Her research areas include the green economy, the relationship between sustainability and economic law, the emergence of green innovations in individual sectors, certain aspects of the circular economy, and the economic aspects of public administrative law.', 1, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=hu&user=UdvgLcYAAAAJ&view_op=list_works&sortby=pubdate', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=56689676500', 'https://https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5330-9050orcid.org/0000-0001-5330-9050', 9, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(192, 'Vasiliki Kolovou', NULL, 'board-member-image/ijerm/6672a24d5813c.IMG_9648.jpeg', 'Hanover University of Applied Sciences and Arts, Hochschule, Hannover', 'Germany', 'Dr. Vasiliki Kolovou holds a Bachelor in Biomedical Sciences from the University of West Attica in Greece, a Master of Public Health and European Public Health from Bielefeld University in Germany and a Ph.D. in Sociology from Warwick University in England. In her doctoral research applied ’’a critical realism approach to public health interventions to prevent obesity in selected European countries.’’. \r\nVasiliki Kolovou is an Associate Professor of Research-based practice in health care in the Faculty of Diaconic Studies, Healthcare and Social Work of Hannover University of Applied Sciences and Arts, teaching, among others, health promotion and disease prevention, international health systems, epidemiology and methods for qualitative research. She has worked with the World Health Organization on various projects related to obesity prevention in communities and with the Institute for Social and Preventive Medicine in Athens. Her research interests are in the field of evaluation of public health interventions promotion of healthy lifestyles in various settings and especially among university students.\r\nShe is an active Member of the European Lifestyle Medicine Organization and a SCOPE-certified professional from the World Obesity Federation.', 1, '', '', '', 10, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(193, 'Steven W. Miller', NULL, 'board-member-image/cie/66750e28937cf.photo.jpg', 'School of Architecture, University of Miami', 'United States', 'Steven W. Miller, FAIA, RIBA, is an accomplished architect with extensive international experience. He recently co-founded INNOVATION Architecture in Coral Gables, collaborating with Gustavo Ribeiro and Ed Mayer. Steven\'s career includes leading Planning And Design Consultants since 1987, with projects in Prague, London, Dubai, and Fort Lauderdale. He has held senior roles at renowned firms like Kohn Pedersen Fox & Perkins Eastman and served as Business Development Sr. Vice President for Shapoorji Pallonji International. Steven has received numerous awards and has been actively involved in the American Institute of Architects (AIA), including serving on various committees and founding international chapters. Additionally, he teaches at the University of Miami and other prestigious institutions, specializing in urban planning, adaptive reuse, and hospitality design.', 4, '', '', '', 7, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(194, 'Claudia Covucci', NULL, 'board-member-image/jblm/6679418181d8b.Photo_Covucci.jpg', 'Faculty of Social and Communication Sciences, Universitas Mercatorum, Piazza Mattei, Rome', 'Italy', '<p>Dr. Claudia Covucci is a Research Fellow at the Faculty of Social and Communication Sciences, Universitas Mercatorum, Rome, Italy, and co-investigator in the PRIN 2022 Project &quot;Entrepreneurial Ecosystem and Business Registration During the COVID-19 Pandemic: A Focus on Female Entrepreneurs&quot;. Her primary research interests concern corporate sustainability, CSR, digital innovation and female entrepreneurship. She has co-authored papers published in leading international academic journals, such as Employee Relations, The Journal of Consumer Marketing, The Journal of Product and Brand Management, Corporate Social Responsibility and Environmental Management and The TQM Journal, and she has collaborated in studies presented at Italian and international conferences.</p>', 5, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=QUmrWaAAAAAJ', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=57203590954', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1837-9736', 18, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(195, 'Shashi Kant Gupta', NULL, 'board-member-image/cie/66794b0b5c1d3.iduUA3BLq95aEDbDJ2Kk1iiI5L7OkmFPHOPHB6cQ.jpg', 'Computer Science and Engineering, Eudoxia Research University, New Castle, Delaware', 'United States', '<p>Dr. Shashi Kant Gupta, Post-Doctoral Fellow and Researcher, Computer Science and Engineering, Eudoxia Research University, USA. He is working as an Honorary Senior Research Fellow at the Department of Scientific Research, Innovation and Training of Scientific and Pedagogical Staff, University of Economics and Pedagogy, Karshi City, Uzbekistan. He is working as a Research Collaborator and Invited Visiting Senior Scientist at the Research Institute of IoT and Cybersecurity, Department of Electronic Engineering, National Kaohsiung University of Science and Technology, Taiwan. He has completed his Ph.D. (CSE) from Integral University, Lucknow, UP, India, &amp; Worked as Assistant Professor in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering, ITM, Lucknow, U.P., India &amp; Worked as Assistant Professor in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering, PSIT, Kanpur, U.P., India, Worked as Associate Professor, School of Computer Applications, BBD University, Lucknow, UP, India, Worked as Assistant Professor, Department of Computer Science and Engineering, Ambalika Institute of Management and Technology, Lucknow, UP, India. &amp; Also worked as Senior Lecturer, Department of IT, MCSCET, Lucknow, UP, India. He is currently working as the Founder and CEO of CREP PVT. LTD., Lucknow, UP, India. He is a member of Spectrum IEEE &amp; Potentials Magazine IEEE since 2019 and many more international organizations for research activities. He is an Editor-in-chief of the International Journal of Data Informatics and Intelligent Computing (IJDIIC) and also Editor-in-chief of the International Journal of Emerging Technologies in Computer and Communication (IJETCC). Senior Editor in Global Research Journal from London Organization of Skill Development, London, United Kingdom. He has published many research papers in reputed international journals, conferences &amp; seminars with SCOPUS and SCI indexing. He has received many awards from many International and national organizations. He has organized various Faculty Development Programs, Seminars, Workshops, and Short-Term Courses at the University level. His main research work focuses on Cloud computing, Big Data Analytics, IoT and Computational Intelligence-based Education. He is currently working as a reviewer and editor in various international journals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 4, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=YGvniSkAAAAJ', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=57461623200', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6587-5607', 9, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(196, 'Zanita E. Fenton', NULL, 'board-member-image/ijerm/667a4d7445478.02202024_JAbreu_483a.jpg', 'School of Law INSERT INTO `journal_board_members` (`id`, `name`, `email`, `image`, `affliation`, `country`, `biography`, `journal_id`, `google_scholar`, `scopus`, `orcid`, `order_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(205, 'Daniel Hicks', 'dhicks@miami.edu', 'board-member-image/CIE/6698b0ed26705.hicks-240x320.png', 'Dept. of Economics Miami Herbert Business School, University of Miami, Coral Gables, Florida', 'United States of America', 'Daniel Hicks is an award-winning university educator, entrepreneur, management consultant, world traveler, veteran journalist and Emmy-nominated network television producer.\r\n\r\nAs a member of the economics faculty at Miami Herbert Business School, Daniel specializes in sustainable business, circularity, integrated corporate reporting, media management and client-based workforce development.\r\n\r\nHe is the founder, organizer and chair of the school\'s annual CSO Summit & Symposium (CSOSS) conference, the longest-running forum of its kind in Florida and the U.S. Southeast.\r\n\r\nAfter more than two decades of producing national television news, the University of California hired Daniel as a senior policy analyst in 2000 to modernize its research communications and media infrastructure. His final report and analysis became a blueprint for the entire UC system and helped to spawn a new cable channel, UCTV. That same year, Daniel launched his own advisory practice, Florida Sustainability Partners LLC (FLSP).\r\n\r\nWhile covering Hollywood in 2004, Daniel created CNBC\'s first-and-only sustainable business series sponsored by Japan\'s Toyota, U.K. oil giant BP and former NBC Universal parent General Electric (Comcast).\r\n\r\nIn 2012, Daniel relocated FLSP to Coral Gables. Embedded at the University of Miami, FLSP was key to launching a top-ranked, interdisciplinary program in sustainable business. His approach combined corporate communications and sustainability with the training of global talent.\r\n\r\nBetween 1988-2009, Daniel produced politics, business and entertainment news from Los Angeles for NBC News, NBC Today, NBC NewsChannel, MSNBC and CNBC. He received Emmy nominations in 2004 (funeral of U.S. President Ronald Reagan) and 1997 (Heaven\'s Gate). In 1998, he covered German elections from Berlin as a correspondent/fellow with the Arthur F. Burns Foundation in Washington, D.C.\r\n\r\nDaniel holds a master’s degree from Columbia University in the City of New York as well as a bachelor’s degree in economics & political science and a professional degree in financial accounting, both from UCLA.', 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, 38, '2024-07-18 10:06:37', '2024-07-18 10:09:12'),
(206, 'Olena Kotykova', 'eikotikova7@gmail.com', 'board-member-image/IJERM/6698f62530fd5.pOcYg3X00iQSG0E48TYMXB0P3N60e0lQD7PgHYDC.png', 'Department of Accounting and Economic Analysis, Admiral Makarov National University of Shipbuilding, Mykolaiv', 'Ukraine', 'Dr. Professor Olena Kotykova currently works in the Department of Accounting and Economic Analysis, Admiral Makarov National University of Shipbuilding (Ukraine). Olena Kotykova, Dr. Professor, is currently a visiting professor at the University of Bamberg (Germany). She received a Master\'s degree in economist-manager, a PhD in economic sciences and a Doctor of economic sciences at Mykolaiv National Agrarian University (Ukraine). The results of her scientific research are presented in more than 150 scientific publications (19 articles in publications indexed by Scopus and/or Web of Science databases), 22 author\'s certificates and 10 monographs. As a leader or member of a scientific or organizational committee, she participated in the organization of more than 20 scientific conferences. As an academic coordinator, she carried out 2 research projects sponsored by the European Commission. She is also President of the Regional Center of European Educational Scientific Enterprises, an Expert of the NAQA and Expert of the National Research Foundation of Ukraine, an Expert of the Scientific Committee of the European DIGITAL SME Alliance, a member of the Association to Excellent Women Academics \"AcademiaNet\". She has been actively engaged in teaching activities for over 25 years. Her attention is focused on sustainable development (SDG 2, 12): agricultural land use, food safety, sustainable food chains, food losses and waste, and circular economy.', 1, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=eEvYKTUAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=35759007600', NULL, 29, '2024-07-18 15:01:57', '2024-07-18 15:01:57');
