(197, 'Jaime E. Correa', NULL, 'board-member-image/cli/667a4fb9e41c7.JAIME CORREA IMAGE.jpg', 'School of Architecture, University of Miami', 'United States', '<p>Jaime Correa is the Director of the Undergraduate Program, an Associate Professor in Practice, and the former Director of the Master of Urban Design (aka: Suburb and Town Design) at the School of Architecture of the University of Miami (position held from 1996 to 2014) where he was also the Knight Professor in Community Building. He currently teaches design, theory, and representation in the Miami and Rome programs of the University of Miami. In 2018, he was a Visiting Professor at Zhuhai College of Jilin University, in China. His paper Practice of Unbuilt Projects (Jaime Correa and Associates) explores the intersection between architecture, art, philosophy, culture, and urbanism. He is one among the 14 architects and town planners who launched the American New Urbanism movement, one of its most important promoters in Latin America and Europe, and one of its most significant critics. From 2013-2017, he served as a Climate Reality Mentor under the tutelage of former Vice-President and Nobel Laureate Al Gore. He is the author of &ldquo;Unbuilt Intentions: towards a new phenomenology of cities and architecture&rdquo;, &ldquo;Redacted Distillations: Le Corbusier&rsquo;s transformative erasures&rdquo;, &ldquo;Seven Recipes for the New Urbanism&rdquo;, &ldquo;Self-sufficient Urbanism&rdquo;, &ldquo;Tales of the Departed&rdquo; and &ldquo;New Harmony: a counterproposal to Charles Fourier&rsquo;s Phalanstery&rdquo;, approximately 17 book chapters, and many articles and papers in peer-reviewed academic journals, newspapers, and magazines.</p>', 2, '', '', '', 3, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(198, 'Qingyang Wu', NULL, 'board-member-image/jblm/667a52115fdfc.LMu0ja4ZddwrCxigsMFErRt2VKRfBXGvTKxlW2Wy.jpg', 'Department of Environmental Health Sciences, Fielding School of Public Health, University of California, Los Angeles', 'United States', '<p>Dr. Wu&#39;s research interests lie at the intersection of environmental science, climate change, and policy. His work primarily focuses on the economic implications of climate change, carbon trading markets, and the impact of emerging technologies on environmental outcomes. He has published extensively in leading journals such as Energy Policy, and Scientific Reports, with several of his papers recognized as ESI Highly Cited Papers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 5, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SZfWD80AAAAJ&hl=en', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=57556847400', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7888-4940', 15, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(199, 'Rakos Ileana - Sorina', NULL, 'board-member-image/jblm/667bc8a20e968.Rakos Ileana.png', 'Faculty of Economic, Administrative and Social Sciences, University of Petrosani', 'Romania', '<p>Dr. Rakos Ileana-Sorina has a robust background in business accounting and public institutions. She is a graduate of the Petroșani University of Economic Studies, Faculty of Economic, Administrative, and Social Sciences. In 2012, she earned her PhD in Economics, focusing her thesis on accounting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since February 2015, Dr. Rakos has been a dedicated lecturer at the Petroșani University of Economic Studies. She teaches courses in Public Procurement, Financial Management of Public Institutions, and Cost Management within the Department of Economic Sciences. Her extensive experience and knowledge in these areas have made her a valuable asset to the university and her students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Rakos has contributed significantly to the academic community through her numerous publications in academic journals. Her research interests are centered on accounting, with a current focus on managerial accounting. She continues to explore and contribute to this critical field, driving forward both academic and practical advancements in accounting.</p>', 5, 'https://scholar.google.ro/citations?hl=en&user=TqryaxYAAAAJ&view_op=list_works&sortby=pubdate', '', '', 33, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(200, 'Cătălin Prodan-Bărbulescu', NULL, 'board-member-image/msr/667be6fcdde7a.Prodan.jpg', 'Discipline of Anatomy and Embriology, “Victor Babeș” University of Medicine and Pharmacy, Timisoara.', 'Romania', '<p>Dr. Cătălin Prodan-Bărbulescu is a Resident Physician specializing in General Surgery at the &quot;Pius Brinzeu&quot; County Emergency Clinical Hospital in Timisoara. He is also an associated teaching staff member in the Department of Anatomy and Embryology at the Victor Babes University of Medicine and Pharmacy Timisoara. As a PhD student, he is actively engaged in research within the Department of Biochemistry and Pharmacology. In addition to his academic and clinical duties, Dr. Prodan-Bărbulescu has volunteered in the COVID-19 Intensive Care Unit at Unfallkrankenhaus Casa Austria, contributing significantly to the fight against the pandemic.</p>', 8, '', '', '', 10, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(201, 'Ramazan Ayaz', NULL, 'board-member-image/seer/66838395a2e24.123.jpg', 'Department of Electrical Engineering, Yildiz Technical University', 'Turkey', '<p>Dr. Ramazan Ayaz is currently an Assistant Professor at the Department of Electrical Engineering, Yildiz Technical University (YTU), Turkey. He received the BSc, M.Sc., and Ph.D. degrees in the Department of Electrical Engineering from the Yildiz Technical University in 2010, 2012 and 2018, respectively. He worked as a researcher at Aalto University, Finland, with a TUBITAK (Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey) Doctoral Research Fellowship in 2015. He is a certified energy manager and certificated energy auditor. His research interests include energy efficiency, photovoltaic systems, advanced lighting technologies, and road lighting. He has published several peer-reviewed articles in esteemed scientific journals. He has also participated in many international conferences in his field. He also has a patent entitled a Warning Sphere with Light.</p>', 4, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=yyknT1gAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao', 'https://www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=55943595400', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6201-1181', 23, '2024-07-17 10:02:51', '2024-07-17 10:02:51'),
(202, 'Francis A. Citera', 'citeraf@gtlaw.com', 'board-member-image/IJERM/6697ab70b0959.Citera_Francis_A.jpg', 'Adjunct Professor, School of Law, University of Miami', 'United States of America', 'Francis A. “Frank” Citera is a nationally recognized trial lawyer representing clients in product liability, toxic torts, class actions, and other complex litigation matters in federal and state courts. Frank is co-chair of the firm’s Product Liability and Mass Torts Litigation Practice and co-chair of the Chicago Litigation Practice. An experienced architect of litigation strategies, Frank defends companies in various industries and business sectors, including retailers such as Albertsons and Claire’s Stores, and technology and electronics companies like Qualcomm, Sony Electronics and UL Solutions. He has achieved success in defeating class certification, disputing alleged claims in court, and obtaining summary judgment and outright dismissals before trial.\r\nFrank is recognized in Chambers USA for Product Liability & Mass Torts (USA – Nationwide) and Litigation: General Commercial (Illinois), where he has been described by clients as being “a gifted litigator but, more than that, he\'s a thoughtful adviser who protects the interests of his client beyond the scope of any particular lawsuit.” The Legal 500 United States described him as “a seasoned lawyer who can solve almost any issue” and who is “tenacious, thoughtful, and intelligent.” Recently, Frank was named an “Ally of the Year” as part of the Corporate Counsel 2023 Women, Influence & Power in Law Awards and was included on the Crain’s Chicago Business 2023 list of Notable Litigators and Trial Attorneys. Frank has also been recognized by The American Lawyer in its “Litigator of the Week” column, for his argument before the Superior Court for the State of Alaska that led to the Court concluding that the State’s claim for public nuisance must fail. Recognized as a thought leader in toxic torts, he serves as an adjunct professor at the University of Miami School of Law teaching toxic torts to the next generation of lawyers.\r\nFrank also advises clients on risk management, crisis management and communications, and product safety matters and has appeared before federal and state agencies such as the Consumer Product Safety Commission, the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, the Food and Drug Administration, and the National Transportation Safety Board.', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 27, '2024-07-17 15:30:56', '2024-07-17 15:30:56'),
(203, 'Maria Pournara', 'maria.pournara@swansea.ac.uk', 'board-member-image/IJERM/6697af70cc556.frDG1yEJFeAOc4fiTC5fx3UywAeKvJQ5EdHLNUbp.jpg', 'Lecturer in Criminology, Swansea University', 'United Kingdom', 'Maria Pournara is a Lecturer in Criminology at Swansea University. Her main research interests are in the areas of policing, organized crime, qualitative research methods, the criminalization of climate change as ecocide, and also pedagogical research, such as the use of AI in HE and embedding employability in HE teaching and learning. She is the student engagement partner for the Department of Criminology, Sociology and Social Policy. She teaches a variety of undergraduate and postgraduate modules. She is an academic mentor and also supervises postgraduate and undergraduate dissertations. She was a Postgraduate Tutor at SOCSI, Cardiff University (2015-19), contributing to seminar and workshop teaching in a variety of criminological as well as social research methods modules. Before focusing on her academic career, she worked as a lawyer in Thessaloniki, Greece, from 2008-2013. Her main practice areas included Human Rights, Civil and Criminal Law. She has an MSc in Crime Analysis (University of Southampton, 2013-2014), an LLM in Criminal Law and Criminology (Democritus University of Thrace, 2008-2012) and an LLB (Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, 2003-2008).', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 28, '2024-07-17 15:48:00', '2024-07-18 08:42:46'),
(204, 'Maria Lorca-Susino', 'mlorca@bus.miami.edu', 'board-member-image/CIE/6697b2ec0060f.FOTO_page-0001.jpg', 'Department of Economics, Miami Herbert Business School, University of Miami, Coral Gables, Florida', 'United States of America', 'Dr. Maria Lorca-Susino received her Ph.D. in International Studies from the University of Miami in 2009. Her research lies in the intersection of macroeconomics, labor economics, and international finance.\r\n\r\nIn 2006, she joined Miami Herbert’s Economics Department, where she has been teaching since. She has published work in top academic journals, presented at leading universities and academic conferences, published two academic books on the economy of the European Union and the euro as a common currency (Routledge Pub.), and is very active in the media, participating regularly as a subject matter expert.', 5, 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=1OgatlkAAAAJ', NULL, NULL, 38, '2024-07-17 16:02:52', '2024-07-17 16:07:30');

